Project: non-toy multi-module fixture for the m7 six-pack.

Two modules with a real boundary: `core` exposes a public API (core/api.sh)
over a private impl (core/lib.sh); `web` composes core but may reach it ONLY
through the public API. Genuine unit tests, an architecture gate, a duplication
gate, and an executable-Gherkin acceptance suite. Deliberately unlike the
sut.sh/42 toy — the declared commands are the project's own entrypoints.

owns:
  core/**
  web/**
  features/**
  acceptance/steps.sh
test: bash run-unit.sh
quality:
  architecture: bash tools/arch-check.sh
  dup: bash tools/dup-check.sh
accept: bash acceptance/run-acceptance.sh
